Subject: [PATCH 1/3] refactor: getGuide sanitizes by default;
 getGuideForTeacher for the editor

The student/public guide fetch now strips the exercise answer key inside
the data-access layer itself, so no caller can accidentally serialize it
to the browser. The guide editor uses the new teacher-gated
getGuideForTeacher, which returns the raw guide (answer key included).
Both return client-serializable plain objects, removing the manual
JSON.parse(JSON.stringify()) + sanitize dance from the pages.
