From b8908da71d7ecfa5d267d1b94ea2fc07b5decf50 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Tue, 9 Jun 2026 21:17:52 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] =?UTF-8?q?feat(quiz):=20exercise=20UX=20=E2=80=94=20e?=
 =?UTF-8?q?xpectations,=20shuffle,=20stale-feedback=20clearing?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- header states the rules up front: question count, pass %, unlimited
  attempts / best score counts
- per-question 'Choose one' / 'Select all that apply' labels
- option display order shuffles per mount (selections keep original
  indices, grading untouched); defeats position-memorization on retries
- changing an answer after grading clears THAT task's stale
  Correct/Incorrect note instead of mislabeling the new answer
- 'N of M answered' next to the disabled submit button explains why it
  is disabled; result banner is aria-live and scrolled into view
- questions are fieldset/legend for screen readers
- component tests cover the meta header, answered count, hint vs
  explanation rendering, and stale-feedback clearing
